40|$|This Master's project {{includes}} the design, development, system integration, and project report for an intelligent exerciser {{specifically designed to}} command an <b>optical</b> <b>memory</b> system. The requirement for the intelligent exerciser is to replace a host computer which normally drives the <b>optical</b> <b>memory</b> as a peripheral device. The operator interface has {{to be easy to}} understand and have a uncomplicated command syntax that is entered in a free format. The intelligent exerciser defines data to be written on the <b>optical</b> <b>memory</b> system, checks data read from the <b>optical</b> <b>memory</b> for correctness, and prints the resulting status of all operator initiated commands and read data. The operator has many choices of what information is to be printed and when it is to be printed. The project includes all hardware and software design of the intelligent exerciser. The project report presents a system overview, system operation as seen by the operator, a detailed hardware design description, and a software description. All schematics and software listings are included. Also included is an operator's manual with detailed instructions on how to enter any <b>optical</b> <b>memory</b> command...|$|E
